<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8599&amp;p=89727#p89727"><![CDATA[
Let me try to rephrase: The reset button of the Famicom is not connected to the PPU. The CPU could come out of reset when the PPU is drawing any dot of any scanline. So don't dwell too much on the first time in the log; just make sure that the successive <em>differences</em> between the times are correct.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Feb 08, 2012 2:21 pm</p><hr />
